SIMPLE: hopeless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hopeless
<hw>Hope"less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Destitute of hope;
having no expectation of good; despairing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I am a woman, friendless, <qex>hopeless</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Giving no ground of hope; promising nothing
desirable; desperate; <as>as, a <ex>hopeless</ex> cause</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>hopeless</qex>word of ⟦ldquo⟧never to return⟦rdquo⟧⟦br⟧
Breathe I against thee, upon pain of life.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Unhoped for; despaired of.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Marston.</au></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Hope"less*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Hope"less*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hoper</ent>⟦br⟧
